dct_title_s: Sketch of North America shewing the proposed route of Capt. Back
dct_description_sm: Fury Pt. where the Fury was lost [1825] and Capt. Ross's intended track [1829] are shown. Proposed water and portage route from New York to Great Slave Lake shown in red. Reported and conjectural coastlines, rivers, and islands shown by dotted lines. From: Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 3 (1833), pp. 64-71; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.3 1833.
dct_publisher_sm: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by John Murray, Albemarle Street, 1833.
